'''國際天主教童軍會議'''（{{lang-en|International Catholic Conference of Scouting, ICCS}}），為一個國際自治團體，主要業務為推廣與支持和天主教會相聯繫的童軍總會，總部位於義大利羅馬。目前轄有800萬名童軍<ref name=Agesci2011>{{cite web |url= http://www.agesci.org/news.php?readmore=290 |title= Elezione Roberto Cociancich |author=AGESCI|authorlink=Associazione Guide e Scouts Cattolici Italiani |date= December 2011 |work=agesci.org |publisher=Agesci |location=Italy |language=it|trans_title=Roberto Cociancich election |accessdate=12 December 2011}}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}</ref>。

該組織於世界童軍委員會享有諮詢地位<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scout.org/en/about_scouting/partners/interreligious/iccs|title=International Catholic Conference of Scouting|publisher=WOSM|accessdate=2010-01-08|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091009091608/http://www.scout.org/en/about_scouting/partners/interreligious/iccs|archivedate=2009-10-09}}</ref>，並與{{le|新教徒童軍與女童軍會|Council of Protestants in Guiding and Scouting}}、{{le|國際正教會童軍連線|International Link of Orthodox Christian Scouts}}、{{le|國際穆斯林童軍聯盟|International Union of Muslim Scouts}}、國際猶太童軍論壇（{{lang|en|International Forum of Jewish Scouts}}）、圓佛教童軍（{{lang|en|Won-Buddhism Scout}}）與{{le|世界佛教童軍兄弟會|World Buddhist Scout Brotherhood}}組成世界童軍泛宗教論壇（{{lang|en|World Scout Inter-religious Forum, WSIF}}）<ref>{{cite web |url=http://wsis2009.org/scouting_wsif.php |title=World Scout Inter-religious Forum (WSIF) |accessdate=2010-01-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090413023825/http://wsis2009.org/scouting_wsif.php |archivedate=2009-04-13 }}</ref>。

該組織與國際天主教女童軍會議（{{lang|en|International Catholic Conference of Guiding, ICCG}}）密切合作<ref>{{cite journal|title=Cooperation with the International Catholic Conference of Guiding|url=http://www.iccs-em.org/sites/default/files/4/attachments/Euro_Med_News_-_Spring_2009.pdf|journal=Euro-Med News|page=4|date=Spring 2009|publisher=ICCS European-Mediterranean region|accessdate=2010-01-08|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120302053837/http://www.iccs-em.org/sites/default/files/4/attachments/Euro_Med_News_-_Spring_2009.pdf|archivedate=2012-03-02}}</ref>。

